Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_histogram_png(25.10)                        create_histogram_png(25.10)

Name
       create_histogram_png - Dumps out the timing histogram image from global
       timing debug in the PNG format without bringing up the GUI

Syntax
       create_histogram_png

       [-help]

       [-height <integer>]

       -name <string>

       [-width <integer>]

       Dumps  out  the  timing histogram image from global timing debug in the
       PNG format without bringing up the GUI. It should open the Global  Tim-
       ing Debug window before the execution of the command. Earlier, this was
       done  when the GUI was displayed by right-clicking the histogram window
       and selecting Snapshot. But that worked only when the snapshot was dis-
       played in the GUI. This command has eliminated the necessity of  bring-
       ing up the GUI to dump out the timing histogram.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each create_histogram_png parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man create_histogram_png

       -height <integer>
              Specifies the height of the PNG image.

              Minimum: 1

              Maximum: 10000

       -name <string>
              Specifies the name of the PNG file.

       -width <integer>
              Specifies the width of the PNG image.

              Minimum: 1

              Maximum: 10000

Related Information
       The Timing Budgeting chapter of the Innovus User Guide document.

